The paper proposes a novel framework for salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves the use of foreground and background cues, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and possibly optimization algorithms (cs.LG). The paper also presents experimental evaluations, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) subcategories.
